1. Definitions

"Software" means the Gigamock source code, documentation, examples, binaries,
and related files distributed with this repository.

"Licensor" means Nikolaj Kuropatkin or another copyright holder that has the
right to license the Software.

"You" means any individual or legal entity using, copying, modifying,
distributing, hosting, selling, or otherwise exploiting the Software.

"Commercial Use" means using the Software, a modified version of the Software,
or a derivative work based on the Software to generate, enable, or materially
support revenue. Commercial Use includes, without limitation:

- selling the Software or a modified version;
- offering the Software as a hosted, managed, SaaS, cloud, consulting,
  integration, testing, QA, developer-platform, or support service;
- bundling the Software into a paid product or paid internal platform;
- using the Software as a material part of a product or service for which
  customers, clients, sponsors, or users pay money.

"Non-Commercial Use" means personal use, educational use, research use,
evaluation, testing, experimentation, and internal use that does not directly or
indirectly generate revenue from the Software or from a product or service based
on the Software.

"Gross Revenue" means all amounts received from Commercial Use before taxes,
fees, hosting costs, salaries, refunds, chargebacks, payment processing fees,
or other deductions.

2. Non-Commercial License Grant

Subject to this license, the Licensor grants You a worldwide, royalty-free,
non-exclusive, non-transferable license to use, copy, modify, and distribute the
Software for Non-Commercial Use.

3. Commercial Revenue Share Requirement

Commercial Use is permitted only if You pay the Licensor five percent (5%) of
Gross Revenue attributable to the Commercial Use of the Software.

Revenue share payments are due monthly, within thirty (30) days after the end
of each calendar month in which Commercial Use generated Gross Revenue.

Before starting Commercial Use, You must make a good-faith effort to contact
the Licensor and agree on payment details. If payment details are not yet
available, the revenue share obligation still applies from the first day of
Commercial Use.

